Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharp turn. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol. Clay fine light red-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie drew seven such stamps (EES XVII). Name Eukleitos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0295.15.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0949)
